<dl id="n06151d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06151d">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06151d"> 151(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> heirs</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;AN INHERITOR OF THE KINGDOM OF HEAVEN.&rdquo;&mdash;And if children, then heirs; heirs of God, and joint heirs with Christ. Jesus Christ the Son of God is the Heir of all things; the children of God by adoption and grace are <mark>heirs</mark> of God, and joint heirs with Christ. <small> Anonymous, <a name="ATCC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ATCC"><cite title="source">Analysis of the Church Catechism</cite></a> (1879) 9</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
